# Build context is experiments/HS-01/ (see Dockerfile header). Paths here are
# therefore relative to experiments/HS-01/, NOT to the app dir.
#
# NOTE: because that context root is the parent dir, BuildKit does not read THIS
# file (it is not at the context root). The build is actually filtered by the
# byte-identical sibling app/Dockerfile.dockerignore, which BuildKit reads next
# to the Dockerfile. This file is kept as the readable, conventionally-named
# copy; edit both together (they must stay identical).
#
# Keep pool_frozen/ and schemas/ IN the context — they are baked into the image.
# Trim everything that would only bloat the context or get rebuilt anyway.

# ── app/ build + dev artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────────────
app/node_modules
app/.next
app/data
app/tests
app/e2e
app/playwright-report
app/test-results
app/*.tsbuildinfo
app/.env
app/.env.local

# Docker / VCS noise
app/Dockerfile
app/Dockerfile.dockerignore
app/.dockerignore
app/docker-compose.yml
**/.git
**/.gitignore

# ── pool_frozen: ship only the bytes the app reads at runtime ─────────────────
# (itempool.json + assets/images are COPYed explicitly; drop the rest.)
pool_frozen/Archive
pool_frozen/report.html
pool_frozen/POOL_README.md

# ── HS-01 dir: nothing else from here is part of the image ────────────────────
__pycache__
**/__pycache__
**/.DS_Store
_logs
data_raw
pool_staging
tests
*.py
*.md
schemas/examples
